From: Strix Halo Packaging <packaging@example.invalid>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add AttrsDescriptor repr for Inductor codegen

Torch Inductor serializes Triton metadata with repr(). Keep the generated code
valid by round-tripping AttrsDescriptor through its existing dictionary form.
---
 python/triton/backends/compiler.py | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/python/triton/backends/compiler.py b/python/triton/backends/compiler.py
index 851d115..2292f6a 100644
--- a/python/triton/backends/compiler.py
+++ b/python/triton/backends/compiler.py
@@ -132,6 +132,9 @@ class AttrsDescriptor:
         key = str(values)
         return hashlib.sha256(key.encode("utf-8")).hexdigest()
 
+    def __repr__(self):
+        return f'AttrsDescriptor.from_dict({self.to_dict()!r})'
+
     def to_dict(self):
         """
         Store the fields of this class in a serializable dictionary
